cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning a projection function from a feature space to a semantic embedding space, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which also suggests the relevance of multimedia (cs.MM) as a possible sub-category.
